cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about using deep learning for vessel segmentation and analysis in 3-D angiographic volumes. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses solutions to problems such as class imbalance and lack of annotated data, which are common in machine learning, making categories such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) likely as well. Finally, the paper uses synthetic data generated by a computational model, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM).
